POWER BI DENEB - MTL MULTI-PRODUCT COMPARISON TIME-SERIES HOVER ADAPTIVE Y-AXIS

This is for the next report page: product comparison.
It supports more than 2 products, uses the same DateKey time-series method as the working product viewer page, adds a hover line with values, and fits the y-axis to selected products.

DATA SOURCE
Use the Excel-generated Final Data sheet/table.

ADD THESE FIELDS TO DENEB VALUES
- Company
- ProductName
- IndexName
- IndexCode
- PR
- Principal
- ProductReturn
- ProductValue
- Volatility
- Formula
- CohortNo
- CohortStartDate
- CohortEndDate
- IndexBaseValue
- Date
- Price
- FXRate
- FXBaseRate
- FXGrowth

SETUP
1. Add a new Deneb visual on the comparison page.
2. Add all fields above from Final Data.
3. Use raw Date, not Date hierarchy.
4. Set numeric fields to Don't summarize.
5. Choose Create new specification > Vega > Empty.
6. Paste only the JSON below.

SLICERS RECOMMENDED
- ProductName: allow multi-select.
- CohortNo: single select or filter to the cohort you want to compare; selected cards display cohort and start date.
- Company: optional.
- Date: optional Between slicer.

ProductReturn drives the product comparison line. If Final Data contains dates after CohortEndDate, page 2 continues to the latest available Final Data date.
Do not limit the Date slicer to CohortEndDate. If the Date slicer ends at CohortEndDate, Power BI hides later calculated rows before Deneb receives them.
The graph displays exactly the rows generated in Final Data, so cohort sampling is controlled by the Excel script: newest 6 daily, older than 6 four points/month + latest, older than 12 two points/month + latest, older than 30 one point/month + latest.

